Find $\tan G$ in the right triangle shown below.

[asy]

pair H,F,G;

H = (0,0);

G = (15,0);

F = (0,8);

draw(F--G--H--F);

draw(rightanglemark(F,H,G,20));

label("$H$",H,SW);

label("$G$",G,SE);

label("$F$",F,N);

label("$17$",(F+G)/2,NE);

label("$15$",G/2,S);

[/asy]

Below is the graph of $y = a \cos bx$ for some positive constants $a$ and $b.$  Find $a.$

[asy]import TrigMacros;

size(400);

real g(real x)
{
	return (3*cos(4*x));
}

draw(graph(g,-3*pi,3*pi,n=700,join=operator ..),red);
trig_axes(-3*pi,3*pi,-4,4,pi/2,1);
layer();
rm_trig_labels(-5, 5, 2);

label("$1$", (0,1), E);
label("$2$", (0,2), E);
label("$3$", (0,3), E);
label("$-1$", (0,-1), E);
label("$-2$", (0,-2), E);
label("$-3$", (0,-3), E);
[/asy]
